WEBVTT

00:01.566 --> 00:02.828
- Previously
on "Superman and Lois"...

00:02.872 --> 00:04.526
- We didn't need your help.

00:04.569 --> 00:06.745
- He and the other
firefighters found ice

00:06.789 --> 00:08.356
inside the store.

00:08.399 --> 00:10.010
Mr. Cushing said that this
is not the first time

00:10.053 --> 00:11.489
that something like this
has happened.

00:11.533 --> 00:13.926
Congratulations, Superboy.
They're onto you.

00:13.970 --> 00:15.798
- I think we put Lex Luthor
in prison

00:15.841 --> 00:17.321
for a crime
he didn't commit.

00:17.365 --> 00:20.107
These victims,
Intergang, Boss Moxie--

00:20.150 --> 00:22.848
Lex Luthor didn't kill them.

00:22.892 --> 00:24.633
- [screaming]

00:24.676 --> 00:26.548
- She's contained.

00:26.591 --> 00:28.941
That'll keep her powers
from working while she's here.

00:28.985 --> 00:31.857
I think it's time that I show
you what I've been working on.

00:31.901 --> 00:33.337
Ever since
your mom's cancer returned...

00:33.381 --> 00:34.991
- Is that Superman?

00:35.035 --> 00:36.819
- It's the Superman
of the Inverse World, son.

00:36.862 --> 00:39.909
It's how I found
the cure to save your mom.

00:41.563 --> 00:44.000
[dramatic music]

00:44.044 --> 00:48.352
- Breast cancer has been
the fight of my life.

00:50.137 --> 00:52.052
And finally,
this part of it,

00:52.095 --> 00:55.011
the chemotherapy,

00:55.055 --> 00:56.621
is over.

00:58.971 --> 01:00.277
- You did it.

01:00.321 --> 01:02.192
- We did it.

01:02.236 --> 01:03.889
But like everything in life,

01:03.933 --> 01:06.327
this journey has not
just been about me.

01:06.370 --> 01:09.069
Cancer affects
many more people

01:09.112 --> 01:11.419
than just the ones
who have it.

01:11.462 --> 01:14.161
It has affected
everyone I love,

01:14.204 --> 01:16.380
especially my family.

01:16.424 --> 01:19.340
But it's because of my family
that I'm standing here today.

01:19.383 --> 01:22.517
You gave me the strength...

01:24.127 --> 01:26.390
And you gave me the hope

01:26.434 --> 01:28.044
that I needed

01:28.088 --> 01:30.002
to see this day.

01:32.527 --> 01:33.919
And I love you all.

01:35.704 --> 01:37.009
Especially you.

01:40.709 --> 01:42.102
Screw cancer!

01:42.145 --> 01:43.973
all: Screw cancer!

01:44.015 --> 01:45.408
[bell ringing]

01:45.453 --> 01:49.109
[cheers and applause]

01:49.152 --> 01:56.158
♪ ♪

02:02.905 --> 02:04.211
- Okay,

02:04.254 --> 02:05.473
I think that's it.

02:05.516 --> 02:07.910
- Where's the Mannheim board?

02:07.953 --> 02:09.693
- [snaps fingers]
[whooshing]

02:10.739 --> 02:12.393
- Thanks, babe.
- Yeah.

02:15.918 --> 02:17.789
You still having
second thoughts?

02:17.833 --> 02:19.356
- I don't think
publishing that story

02:19.400 --> 02:21.271
was the right thing to do.

02:21.315 --> 02:22.664
- Well, after
the Henry Miller attack,

02:22.707 --> 02:23.795
we didn't have a choice.

02:23.839 --> 02:24.927
It put the pressure on Bruno.

02:24.970 --> 02:26.363
- But he still hasn't returned

02:26.407 --> 02:27.886
what he stole from the DOD.

02:27.930 --> 02:29.236
- If he wants to see
his wife, he will.

02:29.279 --> 02:30.889
- It's not right.
Peia's dying.

02:30.933 --> 02:32.021
- Hey, I don't like it either,

02:32.064 --> 02:33.501
but your dad won't budge.

02:33.543 --> 02:35.372
I mean, he barely agreed
to let Matteo visit.

02:35.416 --> 02:36.982
- Maybe he'll change his mind

02:37.026 --> 02:39.507
if I can get
a confession out of Peia.

02:39.550 --> 02:42.249
- She hasn't spoken a word
since the arrest.

02:42.292 --> 02:44.860
- She might to me,
and if nothing else,

02:44.903 --> 02:46.817
at least I can say
what I wanna say to her.

02:48.298 --> 02:50.648
You wanna come?

02:50.692 --> 02:52.563
- I think I'm gonna stay.

02:52.607 --> 02:55.000
I've hardly spent any time
with the boys lately.

02:55.043 --> 02:56.785
Feel like we could use
a good father-son hang.

02:56.828 --> 02:57.916
- That's a good idea.

02:57.960 --> 02:59.309
Do something fun.

02:59.353 --> 03:00.310
- Yeah.

03:00.354 --> 03:05.489
♪ ♪

03:05.533 --> 03:07.796
- Okay, what do you think?

03:07.839 --> 03:09.711
- You look pretty.
- I like the dress better.

03:09.754 --> 03:11.234
- Red's a power color.

03:11.278 --> 03:13.367
I want the governor
to see me as a leader.

03:13.410 --> 03:14.803
- You're the mayor, Mom.

03:14.846 --> 03:16.370
You're kind of
the leader by default.

03:16.413 --> 03:18.589
- Kerry Wexler is a big deal.

03:18.633 --> 03:20.809
I mean, a successful
businesswoman,

03:20.852 --> 03:22.550
a single mother.

03:22.593 --> 03:25.466
If I do this right, it could
lead to big things for us--

03:25.509 --> 03:26.858
state senator,

03:26.902 --> 03:28.773
maybe even Congress.

03:30.122 --> 03:31.863
Regardless,

03:31.907 --> 03:34.866
it's a chance for Smallville
to get some good press.

03:34.910 --> 03:38.000
- Uh, is the "Gazette"
covering the visit?

03:38.043 --> 03:40.089
- Yeah, Chrissy is.

03:40.132 --> 03:42.613
- That gonna be weird?

03:42.656 --> 03:44.572
The mayor's ex-husband's
new girlfriend

03:44.615 --> 03:46.095
just hanging around all day?

03:46.138 --> 03:47.792
- No, it's not like
their relationship's

03:47.836 --> 03:49.707
gonna come up.
It'll be fine.

03:49.751 --> 03:51.840
Okay, good to go?

03:51.883 --> 03:53.711
- Definitely.
- You're gonna kill it, Mom.

03:55.974 --> 03:58.454
- Mwah. Your abuela's gonna
come pick you up in an hour.

03:58.499 --> 03:59.935
What are you doing today?

03:59.978 --> 04:01.763
- I don't know,
probably just nothing.

04:01.806 --> 04:03.504
- All right, well,
text me if you go somewhere.

04:04.940 --> 04:06.202
[phone chimes and buzzes]

04:06.246 --> 04:13.078
♪ ♪

04:15.385 --> 04:17.344
- With this stall
in the Mannheim investigation,

04:17.387 --> 04:19.302
there is barely enough stories

04:19.346 --> 04:21.826
to fill out tomorrow's paper.

04:21.870 --> 04:25.439
- Well, can't you
just use AP stuff?

04:25.482 --> 04:26.744
- I guess.

04:26.788 --> 04:28.746
Maybe this meeting
with Governor Wexler

04:28.790 --> 04:30.400
will give me 2,000 words.

04:30.444 --> 04:31.532
- [chuckles]

04:34.709 --> 04:36.188
I may have something.

04:36.232 --> 04:37.451
- Oh, yeah?

04:37.494 --> 04:39.017
[chuckles]
- Yup.

04:39.061 --> 04:42.456
So this is Fowe's.

04:42.499 --> 04:46.024
Right? And all that ice,
that just, uh, appeared

04:46.068 --> 04:49.071
after the fire
was mysteriously extinguished.

04:49.114 --> 04:52.596
Same thing happened
last year at the town hall.

04:52.640 --> 04:55.338
Someone in Smallville
has powers.

04:55.382 --> 04:57.514
I think this is what you
should be writing about.

04:59.560 --> 05:01.344
- Sorry, but I--
[chuckles]

05:01.388 --> 05:03.607
I can't publish any of this.

05:03.651 --> 05:05.522
- Seriously?

05:05.566 --> 05:07.350
I think it's a pretty big deal,Chrissy.

05:07.394 --> 05:09.831
- [chuckles]
I mean, you have no proof.

05:09.874 --> 05:10.919
- This is the proof.

05:10.962 --> 05:13.443
- This looks like Freon.

05:13.487 --> 05:15.793
A--a refrigerator
probably burst or something.

05:15.837 --> 05:18.970
- It's not refrigerant.
I would've smelled that.

05:19.014 --> 05:21.451
- Even if this person was real,

05:21.495 --> 05:22.800
all they've done is help.

05:24.585 --> 05:26.326
Why go to all the trouble
to expose them?

05:27.892 --> 05:29.241
- After everything
that we've been through

05:29.285 --> 05:30.678
in Smallville,
don't you think

05:30.721 --> 05:32.027
that we deserve the truth?

05:32.070 --> 05:35.335
♪ ♪

05:35.378 --> 05:36.683
[sighs]

05:36.727 --> 05:39.730
Look, babe,
I--I--I'm no journalist.

05:39.774 --> 05:41.515
okay, but...

05:41.558 --> 05:44.126
I think this is
a really big story.

05:44.169 --> 05:45.954
- [chuckles]

05:45.997 --> 05:49.305
Well, let me be the one
who decides that, okay?

05:51.133 --> 05:52.700
[clears throat]

05:52.743 --> 05:54.528
- Okay, then.

05:54.571 --> 05:55.877
- Kyle--
- No, no, it's fine.

05:55.920 --> 05:58.706
I'll let you get back to it.

05:58.749 --> 06:00.403
[door clicks shut]

06:00.447 --> 06:02.231
- Where you going?
- Come on, get on it.

06:02.274 --> 06:03.537
- Come on, what are you doing?
- Go, go, go.

06:03.580 --> 06:04.929
- Come on, catch him,
catch him.

06:04.973 --> 06:07.018
- Go! Touchdown!
- No, I had you!

06:07.062 --> 06:09.760
Bro, I literally had you!
- Hey, guys.

06:09.804 --> 06:12.284
- [laughs] Your D's weaker
than you without superpowers.

06:12.328 --> 06:13.634
- Says the guy
with two fumbles.

06:13.677 --> 06:14.678
- Jon, Jordan.

06:14.722 --> 06:16.985
- Hey, Dad.
- Hey.

06:17.028 --> 06:19.074
I was thinking the three of us
could, uh, hang out today--

06:19.117 --> 06:20.336
you know, do something fun,

06:20.380 --> 06:22.730
maybe see a movie
or fly somewhere?

06:22.773 --> 06:23.948
- Yeah, cool.

06:26.951 --> 06:28.475
- Anything fun
you guys wanna do?

06:28.518 --> 06:30.520
- I don't know, not really.

06:30.564 --> 06:32.000
- Okay.

06:32.043 --> 06:33.436
How 'bout this?
I come up with something,

06:33.480 --> 06:34.959
and then we do that.

06:35.003 --> 06:36.134
Sound good?

06:36.178 --> 06:37.135
- Sure.

06:37.179 --> 06:38.223
- Okay, cool.

06:39.747 --> 06:40.748
- Great.

06:42.140 --> 06:43.228
- Here's the handoff.
[whistle blows]

06:43.272 --> 06:44.534
- By the way,
my D's next-level.

06:44.578 --> 06:46.493
- [scoffs]
[phone chimes and buzzes]

06:49.017 --> 06:51.889
Yo, there's a senior kegger
at the old fairgrounds.

06:51.933 --> 06:53.195
We should go.

06:53.238 --> 06:54.196
- I mean, we don't really have

06:54.239 --> 06:55.763
any friends who are seniors.

06:55.806 --> 06:57.025
- So we'll make friends.

06:57.068 --> 06:58.592
Besides, Sarah's going.

06:58.635 --> 07:00.768
- What?
Sarah texted you?

07:00.811 --> 07:03.640
- Yeah, because, A,
we're friends,

07:03.684 --> 07:05.686
and, B, you won't stop
barfing out

07:05.729 --> 07:07.078
how much you're in love
with her.

07:07.122 --> 07:08.428
- That's only, like, half true.

07:08.471 --> 07:09.907
- Okay.

07:09.951 --> 07:12.649
The fairgrounds are so far
outside of town.

07:12.693 --> 07:14.434
I'm gonna call Candice.

07:14.477 --> 07:16.436
Maybe she can make
the drive down in time.

07:16.479 --> 07:18.568
- I--I mean, we just
made plans with Dad.

07:18.612 --> 07:20.135
- Yeah, so what?

07:20.178 --> 07:22.746
He cancels on us all the time
for Superman stuff.

07:22.790 --> 07:26.010
♪ ♪

07:26.054 --> 07:28.317
- Single player, I guess.

07:33.191 --> 07:34.628
[elevator bell dings]

07:34.671 --> 07:35.846
- Matteo.

07:37.979 --> 07:40.895
[tense music]

07:40.938 --> 07:42.549
♪ ♪

07:42.592 --> 07:44.638
Follow me.

07:44.681 --> 07:51.688
♪ ♪

07:54.082 --> 07:56.824
You don't need
to be nervous, son.

07:56.867 --> 07:59.043
- I just wish
you were coming too.

07:59.087 --> 08:00.958
- Better that I don't.

08:01.002 --> 08:02.960
This way,

08:03.004 --> 08:05.397
you can be alone
with your mother.

08:05.441 --> 08:07.269
- But, Dad, I don't know
if I could do this.

08:07.312 --> 08:09.140
Like--
- Your mother's dying, Matteo.

08:11.882 --> 08:15.190
Now, I know it's gonna be hard

08:15.233 --> 08:16.974
to see her like this,

08:17.018 --> 08:20.848
but...she needs you.

08:20.891 --> 08:22.980
We both do.

08:25.026 --> 08:26.680
- Yeah.

08:26.723 --> 08:29.639
♪ ♪

08:29.683 --> 08:30.988
I'm ready.

08:35.732 --> 08:37.125
- I don't know about this,
man.

08:37.168 --> 08:38.386
He seemed
pretty excited to hang.

08:38.429 --> 08:40.128
- Just let me handle it, okay?

08:40.171 --> 08:41.259
I'll let him down easy.

08:41.303 --> 08:42.652
[whooshing]

08:42.696 --> 08:44.131
- Who wants
to wrangle and tangle?

08:44.174 --> 08:45.568
Huh?
[laughs]

08:45.612 --> 08:47.222
Tonight!

08:47.265 --> 08:49.572
Wrestle Rumble 40
in Metropolis,

08:49.616 --> 08:51.400
no holds barred!

08:51.443 --> 08:53.184
- Did you buy a shirt?
- Yeah!

08:53.228 --> 08:55.317
It's Bam the Bulldozer!

08:55.360 --> 08:57.101
Guys, come on!

08:57.145 --> 08:59.103
We used to go all the time
when we lived in Metropolis.

09:00.583 --> 09:02.106
- Good luck, Jon.

09:02.150 --> 09:04.326
- W--what's going on?

09:04.369 --> 09:05.936
- Uh, well,

09:05.980 --> 09:08.199
that sounds cool, uh, but we

09:08.243 --> 09:10.332
kind of already have plans.

09:10.375 --> 09:12.595
- What?
I thought we had plans.

09:12.639 --> 09:14.858
- Well, I mean,
we had plans to have plans,

09:14.902 --> 09:16.860
but now something's come up.

09:16.904 --> 09:18.558
Candice was gonna come down,

09:18.601 --> 09:19.907
and we were gonna hang
with her and Sarah.

09:19.950 --> 09:22.387
- Yeah, just super low-key.

09:22.431 --> 09:23.911
- Okay, well, have them join.

09:23.954 --> 09:25.390
- Dad.

09:25.434 --> 09:26.783
- What? I--I just thought
it'd be fun for us

09:26.827 --> 09:28.263
to all spend some time
together.

09:28.306 --> 09:29.960
- Yeah, well,
we'll do something else

09:30.004 --> 09:31.396
more fun real soon.

09:31.440 --> 09:33.137
I promise.

09:34.399 --> 09:36.619
We kind of have to get going.

09:38.099 --> 09:41.015
- Okay, yeah.
Um, um, tell the girls hi.

09:41.058 --> 09:43.147
- Thanks anyway, Dad.
- Mm-hmm.

09:45.019 --> 09:47.369
- Not sure you're gonna get
the results you wanted there.

09:49.023 --> 09:51.112
- I need to make this right.

09:51.155 --> 09:53.767
- It's not about you, pumpkin.
It's about her.

09:53.810 --> 09:56.639
I'm afraid Peia Mannheim's
not long for this world.

09:56.683 --> 09:58.685
- That's why it's time
for her to come clean.

10:00.121 --> 10:02.036
- My experience,

10:02.079 --> 10:04.125
person keeps
a secret long enough,

10:04.168 --> 10:06.040
sometimes the truth is lost--

10:06.083 --> 10:07.607
even to them.

10:07.650 --> 10:14.657
♪ ♪

10:17.138 --> 10:21.403
[power dampener thrumming]

10:24.667 --> 10:27.104
- I was hoping you were Matteo.

10:27.148 --> 10:29.498
- Just me for now.

10:29.541 --> 10:34.285
♪ ♪

10:38.202 --> 10:39.682
Are you comfortable?

10:39.726 --> 10:41.249
- [chuckles]

10:41.292 --> 10:43.207
As much as I can be.

10:43.251 --> 10:46.646
The doctors here have
some really good painkillers.

10:49.518 --> 10:51.999
You all done with chemo?

10:52.042 --> 10:54.479
- Yeah, rang the bell
and everything.

10:54.523 --> 10:55.655
- Hmm.

10:55.698 --> 10:57.569
- My mastectomy is in two days.

10:57.613 --> 10:59.093
- Mm.

10:59.136 --> 11:00.442
You feeling nervous?

11:00.485 --> 11:02.618
- I was a mess.
[chuckles]

11:02.662 --> 11:04.968
I feel better now.

11:05.012 --> 11:06.187
Still...

11:06.230 --> 11:08.102
- Yeah.

11:08.145 --> 11:09.669
It's hard to put in words

11:09.712 --> 11:11.366
what that's like.

11:11.409 --> 11:13.629
- I missed having you
to talk to.

11:15.152 --> 11:18.808
- Guess cancer
does make strange bedfellows.

11:18.852 --> 11:20.549
[chuckles]

11:22.638 --> 11:24.640
- Which is why I wanted
to give you the opportunity

11:24.684 --> 11:26.424
to set the record straight.

11:28.470 --> 11:30.037
- [sighs]

11:30.080 --> 11:31.952
- Just hear me out.

11:31.995 --> 11:35.172
Things are going to get written
about you, no matter what.

11:35.216 --> 11:37.784
This is your one chance
to tell your side of the story.

11:37.827 --> 11:39.699
- And what's that story?

11:39.742 --> 11:41.483
Hmm?

11:41.526 --> 11:43.267
A superpowered monster

11:43.311 --> 11:45.400
who's been running loose
in Hob's Bay?

11:45.443 --> 11:47.489
- Is that really
how you see yourself?

11:47.532 --> 11:48.925
'Cause the woman I know

11:48.969 --> 11:50.579
is a lot more complicated
than that.

11:51.841 --> 11:53.147
She's a devoted wife,

11:53.190 --> 11:56.628
a loving mother,

11:56.672 --> 11:58.674
a friend.

11:58.718 --> 12:00.241
Let me tell your story, Peia.

12:00.284 --> 12:02.243
I promise I'll be fair.

12:02.286 --> 12:05.463
[somber music]

12:05.507 --> 12:07.030
- [sighs]

12:07.074 --> 12:14.081
♪ ♪

12:16.518 --> 12:17.562
Okay.

12:20.130 --> 12:21.131
Okay.

12:21.175 --> 12:22.524
[phone recorder dings]

12:22.567 --> 12:28.573
♪ ♪

12:28.617 --> 12:31.228
- Hey. My God,
I'm so glad you're here.

12:31.272 --> 12:32.926
- The governor's
arriving any minute.

12:32.969 --> 12:34.710
- I know, but first,
we need to talk about Kyle.

12:34.754 --> 12:36.843
- Chrissy.
- There's a problem.

12:36.886 --> 12:38.758
- Which is now your problem.

12:38.801 --> 12:40.411
I've been supportive
of this relationship,

12:40.455 --> 12:41.717
but I'm not gonna be
tech support

12:41.761 --> 12:43.284
on how to deal with Kyle.

12:43.327 --> 12:44.589
- No, it's actually about...
- She's here.

12:49.420 --> 12:50.595
- The secret.

12:52.467 --> 12:54.730
- Governor Wexler,
it's an honor.

12:54.774 --> 12:57.341
- Mayor Lang, thank you
so much for having me.

12:57.385 --> 13:00.692
Hope you don't mind. I let some
of the press know I was coming.

13:00.736 --> 13:02.390
Ah, I see you've got
one of your own.

13:02.433 --> 13:03.739
- Oh, you know Chrissy Beppo

13:03.783 --> 13:06.002
from the "Smallville Gazette."

13:06.046 --> 13:07.743
- The newspaper that disagreed

13:07.787 --> 13:11.181
with my school tax bill.

13:11.225 --> 13:15.055
Now, how about you walk me
through what happened here?

13:15.098 --> 13:18.058
[rock music]

13:18.101 --> 13:20.234
♪ ♪

13:20.277 --> 13:22.236
- Well, gotta hand it to you.

13:22.279 --> 13:24.281
Many people have tried,
but you're the first person

13:24.325 --> 13:26.283
to actually rip
Superman's heart out.

13:26.327 --> 13:28.546
- Yeah, yeah, okay.

13:29.504 --> 13:31.680
- Jonathan.

13:31.723 --> 13:33.769
[laughs]
Hey, babe.

13:33.813 --> 13:35.771
- You made it.

13:35.815 --> 13:37.904
- Peggy's sister Nancy
was super sweet,

13:37.947 --> 13:39.427
and she let me borrow her car.

13:39.470 --> 13:40.428
- Hi, Candice.

13:40.471 --> 13:42.343
- Hey.

13:42.386 --> 13:43.431
- Maybe I should
send Aunt Nancy

13:43.474 --> 13:45.172
a thank-you letter.

13:45.215 --> 13:46.738
- Maybe you should.

13:48.566 --> 13:51.787
- I'm gonna--
I'm gonna go find Sarah.

13:51.831 --> 13:58.620
♪ ♪

13:58.663 --> 14:02.667
[indistinct chatter]

14:02.711 --> 14:06.062
- Yeah. Yeah.
- [chuckles]

14:06.106 --> 14:08.630
But it wasn't my mattress!
- [laughs]

14:08.673 --> 14:11.328
- Whose was it?

14:11.372 --> 14:14.070
- Uh, Vanessa's.

14:14.114 --> 14:15.550
- It's a long story.

14:15.593 --> 14:18.074
Uh, did you ever tell them
where it came from?

14:18.118 --> 14:19.728
- No, 'cause I'd already
spent the 60 bucks.

14:19.771 --> 14:21.512
- [laughs]
- What'd you spend it on?

14:23.166 --> 14:24.864
- It's not really important.

14:26.387 --> 14:27.954
- Hey, uh,
why don't you go grab a beer

14:27.997 --> 14:29.433
while Junior
finishes his story?

14:29.477 --> 14:30.739
- Yeah, man.

14:30.782 --> 14:32.741
They don't ID here.
You'll be good.

14:34.917 --> 14:36.136
- Okay.

14:38.268 --> 14:40.053
- So the boys didn't wanna
hang out with you, huh?

14:40.096 --> 14:41.968
- Yeah, they said
something came up.

14:42.011 --> 14:44.187
- [scoffs]
Yeah, I bet it did.

14:44.231 --> 14:46.015
- All right, all right.

14:46.059 --> 14:47.408
Like, I--

14:47.451 --> 14:48.931
I finally have time
to hang out with them,

14:48.975 --> 14:50.454
and they couldn't
get away from me fast enough.

14:50.498 --> 14:52.282
- They're teenage boys.

14:52.326 --> 14:55.807
Hanging out with boring old Dad
just isn't a priority,

14:55.851 --> 14:57.897
even if their dad
is you-know-who.

14:59.507 --> 15:01.117
- Feel like some people
would think that's pretty cool.

15:01.161 --> 15:02.727
- Yeah, well,
those people aren't your sons.

15:02.771 --> 15:04.773
- Yeah.
- You, Clark,

15:04.816 --> 15:07.341
are fast approaching
the obsolescence phase

15:07.384 --> 15:09.604
of fatherhood.

15:09.647 --> 15:12.433
Just be glad
they don't hate you.

15:12.476 --> 15:14.478
For most of us,
that's considered a win.

15:16.654 --> 15:20.136
- How's it going in there?
- Mm, a lot of backstory,

15:20.180 --> 15:23.226
feelin' all sorry for herself.

15:23.270 --> 15:27.013
But I think Lois is about
to get her on the hook.

15:27.056 --> 15:28.928
[device blips]

15:28.971 --> 15:31.800
- Did Boss Moxie ever find out
about you and Bruno?

15:31.843 --> 15:33.236
- No.

15:33.280 --> 15:35.108
We managed to keep it a secret.

15:35.151 --> 15:37.849
- He must've been
suspicious, though.

15:37.893 --> 15:39.764
- Hard--hard to say.

15:39.808 --> 15:40.896
- Why is that?

15:40.940 --> 15:43.072
- We weren't actually dating

15:43.116 --> 15:45.422
for very long before...
[coughs]

15:45.466 --> 15:49.035
Boss was murdered
by Lex Luthor.

15:49.078 --> 15:50.427
- I see.

15:50.471 --> 15:53.909
[dramatic music]

15:53.953 --> 15:55.911
I listened to Luthor's
confession again,

15:55.955 --> 15:57.521
and I don't think
it was him on that tape.

15:57.565 --> 15:58.870
I think it was you.

16:00.350 --> 16:02.352
- He had a motive.

16:02.396 --> 16:03.788
- So did you and Bruno.

16:05.529 --> 16:07.923
The way that Moxie
and his men were murdered,

16:07.967 --> 16:09.316
your powers did that.

16:09.359 --> 16:10.970
- I don't know
what you're talking about.

16:11.013 --> 16:12.623
- It's the only thing
that makes sense, Peia.

16:12.667 --> 16:14.669
You and Bruno
killed Boss Moxie,

16:14.712 --> 16:16.758
took over Hob's Bay,

16:16.801 --> 16:18.238
and you used Luthor
as your fall guy.

16:18.281 --> 16:21.328
♪ ♪

16:21.371 --> 16:23.286
- Have you ever been
in a room alone

16:23.330 --> 16:25.941
with Lex Luthor?

16:25.985 --> 16:27.377
He has this aura.

16:27.421 --> 16:29.249
It's terrifying,

16:29.292 --> 16:33.296
like you're in the presence
of the devil himself.

16:33.340 --> 16:35.690
To this day, that man
is the only person in the world

16:35.733 --> 16:37.213
who scares me.

16:37.257 --> 16:39.650
- But he didn't kill
Moxie or his men.

16:39.694 --> 16:41.261
You did.
- I can tell you

16:41.304 --> 16:42.871
about a dozen other crimes

16:42.914 --> 16:44.612
Luthor committed
that are far worse

16:44.655 --> 16:46.092
than what happened to Boss.

16:46.135 --> 16:48.355
- Peia.
- Don't do this, Lois.

16:48.398 --> 16:50.183
- I helped put a man
behind bars

16:50.226 --> 16:51.662
for a crime
he didn't commit.

16:51.706 --> 16:54.448
- And the world
is better for it.

16:54.491 --> 16:57.755
Lex Luthor was a monster
before he went to prison.

16:57.799 --> 17:00.149
Can you imagine
what he's become since?

17:01.759 --> 17:04.719
Setting him free
would be the biggest mistake

17:04.762 --> 17:06.025
of your life.

17:07.678 --> 17:08.896
- That's not a denial.

17:08.940 --> 17:10.116
- [scoffs]

17:10.159 --> 17:12.335
We're done here.

17:12.378 --> 17:14.076
- Peia,
please tell me the truth.

17:14.119 --> 17:16.992
- [breathes heavily]

17:17.036 --> 17:20.039
Thanks for visiting, Lois.

17:20.082 --> 17:21.474
Don't come back.

17:21.518 --> 17:28.089
♪ ♪

17:31.224 --> 17:33.965
[power dampener thrums]

17:38.579 --> 17:40.581
[rock music playing]

17:40.624 --> 17:43.888
[indistinct chatter]

17:43.932 --> 17:48.545
♪ ♪

17:48.589 --> 17:51.200
- I think that keg is tapped.

17:51.244 --> 17:53.115
Here.

17:53.159 --> 17:54.769
[sighs]

17:56.858 --> 17:58.729
Okay, can you not do the whole

17:58.773 --> 18:00.601
sad-boy thing right now?

18:00.644 --> 18:04.213
- Just admit it.
That guy Junior's a dick.

18:04.257 --> 18:07.390
- His dad was murdered.
Cut him some slack.

18:07.434 --> 18:09.436
- He's still a dick.

18:11.177 --> 18:13.222
- So is this what being friends
with you is like?

18:13.266 --> 18:15.616
Just getting pissy every time
I'm talking to another guy?

18:15.659 --> 18:17.270
- That's not it.
- Then what is it?

18:17.313 --> 18:18.706
- It's because you looked
annoyed that I came

18:18.749 --> 18:19.924
to talk to you
when you were with him.

18:19.968 --> 18:21.143
- You barged
into our conversation

18:21.187 --> 18:22.710
while he was telling a story.

18:22.753 --> 18:24.625
- You shooed me away.
- Oh, my God.

18:24.668 --> 18:25.930
Get over yourself.

18:28.324 --> 18:31.110
Stop making me feel weird
whenever I'm around you.

18:33.416 --> 18:35.505
- You know,
sometimes I really wish

18:35.549 --> 18:37.203
I never fell in love
with you.

18:40.162 --> 18:42.077
- That makes two of us.

18:42.121 --> 18:46.777
♪ ♪

18:46.821 --> 18:48.214
[indistinct yelling]

18:48.257 --> 18:49.650
- Well, it's certainly
going to take a while

18:49.693 --> 18:51.217
to recover from this.

18:51.260 --> 18:54.263
- Well, the plan
is to not let that happen.

18:54.307 --> 18:56.526
To supplement
insurance claims,

18:56.570 --> 19:00.356
we're utilizing all
rural disaster development aid.

19:00.400 --> 19:02.750
I've met with all
the store owners,

19:02.793 --> 19:04.099
and we've agreed

19:04.143 --> 19:06.014
to focus
all the resources

19:06.057 --> 19:08.451
on the businesses
impacted most.

19:08.495 --> 19:10.105
- Hmm.
[horn honks]

19:10.149 --> 19:11.672
- Hey, Governor.

19:11.715 --> 19:13.543
- Great little community
you've got here.

19:13.587 --> 19:14.805
- Yeah.

19:14.849 --> 19:15.980
Been in Smallville

19:16.024 --> 19:17.634
my whole life for a reason.

19:17.678 --> 19:19.506
- Helps when you've got
good leadership,

19:19.549 --> 19:21.682
people with their eyes
toward the future.

19:21.725 --> 19:23.988
- Well, just trying
to do my best.

19:24.032 --> 19:25.555
- You're succeeding.

19:25.599 --> 19:28.732
People are taking note--
people like me.

19:28.776 --> 19:30.517
Single mom, right?

19:30.560 --> 19:32.345
- As of recently, yes.

19:32.388 --> 19:33.955
- Ah, let me guess.

19:33.998 --> 19:37.306
He got bored and traded you in
for some young floozy?

19:37.350 --> 19:39.090
Oh, don't be embarrassed.

19:39.134 --> 19:40.570
I've got the same story--

19:40.614 --> 19:43.182
best thing that ever happened.

19:43.225 --> 19:44.922
I realized pretty quickly
the only thing

19:44.966 --> 19:46.924
that cheating son of a bitch
was doing was holding me back.

19:46.968 --> 19:50.232
No, you get a bunch
of single moms in charge,

19:50.276 --> 19:52.974
badasses like you and me,

19:53.017 --> 19:56.804
we'll fix this state up
pretty quick.

19:56.847 --> 19:59.110
Now, uh, I hear you can get

19:59.154 --> 20:02.113
a mean piece
of rhubarb pie in town.

20:02.157 --> 20:03.114
- Follow me.

20:03.158 --> 20:06.422
[dramatic music]

20:06.466 --> 20:08.555
[rock music playing]

20:08.598 --> 20:10.252
- So you still
haven't seen your dad?

20:10.296 --> 20:12.341
- I mean, he's called
a few times, but...

20:12.385 --> 20:13.603
- You know where he is?

20:13.647 --> 20:16.171
- Um, Kansas City, I think.

20:16.215 --> 20:17.477
I'm not sure.

20:17.520 --> 20:19.218
Honestly, it's, uh,
not the first time

20:19.261 --> 20:21.045
he's vanished, so...

20:21.089 --> 20:22.699
- That sucks.

20:22.743 --> 20:24.397
- People are who they are,
I guess.

20:26.050 --> 20:27.965
But, uh,
how's the fire station?

20:28.009 --> 20:30.141
- Oh, it's fine.

20:30.185 --> 20:32.666
- Wait, last time we talked
about it, you were so excited.

20:32.709 --> 20:34.537
What happened?
- Nothing.

20:34.581 --> 20:38.019
Uh, Mr. Cushing just wants me
to take a break for a bit.

20:38.062 --> 20:39.586
- Why would he want that?

20:41.196 --> 20:43.416
- Can we just, um--
can we not talk about it?

20:43.459 --> 20:46.854
- Oh, uh, sure,
if that's what you really want.

20:46.897 --> 20:51.902
♪ ♪

20:51.946 --> 20:54.601
[indistinct chatter]

20:54.644 --> 20:59.606
♪ ♪

20:59.649 --> 21:02.478
- It--it sucks
not having you here.

21:03.784 --> 21:05.786
It's been tough.

21:05.829 --> 21:07.396
- I miss you too, babe.

21:07.440 --> 21:09.485
♪ ♪

21:09.529 --> 21:11.313
[high-pitched warbling]

21:11.357 --> 21:13.533
[engine revving]

21:13.576 --> 21:17.667
[tires squealing,
siren wailing]

21:17.711 --> 21:19.060
- Sheriff!
- Sheriff!

21:19.103 --> 21:20.801
- Go, go, go,
go, go, go, go.

21:20.844 --> 21:23.804
- Go, go, go!

21:23.847 --> 21:25.719
- This is
the Sheriff's Department.

21:25.762 --> 21:28.199
Everyone remain where you are.

21:28.243 --> 21:30.201
- Hold it right there!

21:30.245 --> 21:31.812
- Go, go, go, go, go, go, go!

21:31.855 --> 21:35.642
♪ ♪

21:35.685 --> 21:37.339
Come on!
- I'm trying.

21:37.383 --> 21:39.210
- I get caught, this will be
my second underage drinking.

21:39.254 --> 21:40.777
- You're not getting caught.

21:40.821 --> 21:42.997
♪ ♪

21:43.040 --> 21:44.433
[engine turning over]
- Kill the lights

21:44.477 --> 21:45.782
so they can't see
which way we went.

21:45.826 --> 21:48.394
[engine roars, tires squeal]

21:48.437 --> 21:55.226
♪ ♪

21:58.839 --> 21:59.753
- Are they following us?

21:59.796 --> 22:01.581
- Um...

22:01.624 --> 22:03.670
I don't think so.
- No?

22:03.713 --> 22:06.455
- No, I think we're good.
[chuckles]

22:06.499 --> 22:09.023
You're, like,
this badass getaway driver.

22:09.066 --> 22:10.590
- That was insane.
- [laughs]

22:10.633 --> 22:11.721
- [laughs]

22:12.896 --> 22:14.158
Oh, my God!
- [screams]

22:14.202 --> 22:16.291
[tires squealing]

22:27.389 --> 22:31.262
[dramatic music]

22:31.306 --> 22:33.177
[sirens wailing]

22:33.221 --> 22:34.744
[whooshing]

22:34.788 --> 22:36.746
♪ ♪

22:36.790 --> 22:38.226
- Did you see that?

22:38.269 --> 22:40.620
Some guy with powers
just saved our lives.

22:40.663 --> 22:43.187
♪ ♪

22:46.539 --> 22:47.583
- Yeah, well,
she tried getting away

22:47.627 --> 22:48.889
by turning off her lights--

22:48.932 --> 22:50.281
just wasn't expecting
a deer in the road

22:50.325 --> 22:51.761
when she cut 'em back on.
- Sarah,

22:51.805 --> 22:53.328
what the hell
were you thinking, huh?

22:53.372 --> 22:54.416
[indistinct radio chatter]

22:54.460 --> 22:56.200
- Listen, Kyle.

22:56.244 --> 22:58.333
I'm willing to drop
fleeing the scene,

22:58.377 --> 23:00.379
but driving
under the influence--

23:00.422 --> 23:01.771
I'm afraid the department

23:01.815 --> 23:03.164
can't just look the other wayon that.

23:03.207 --> 23:04.861
We're gonna charge her
with a DUI.

23:04.905 --> 23:06.341
- Yeah, I understand.

23:06.385 --> 23:08.082
Uh, listen, you have my word

23:08.125 --> 23:09.475
that her mom and I
will make sure

23:09.518 --> 23:12.303
nothing like this
ever happens again.

23:12.347 --> 23:13.957
- Thankfully, no one got hurt.

23:14.001 --> 23:15.785
People usually don't walk away
from a wreck like this.

23:15.829 --> 23:17.787
- That's because
somebody saved us.

23:17.831 --> 23:19.615
- Junior.
- No, not this again.

23:21.704 --> 23:23.663
- Hold on, now.
What--what makes you say that?

23:23.706 --> 23:25.316
- Because just as
we started to crash,

23:25.360 --> 23:26.883
there was, like, this blur,
and then suddenly,

23:26.927 --> 23:28.581
we're on the side of the road.

23:28.624 --> 23:30.583
When I looked up, there was
some guy standing there,

23:30.626 --> 23:32.628
but then the sheriff showed,
and he just vanished.

23:32.672 --> 23:33.890
[dramatic music]

23:33.934 --> 23:35.675
- Did you see
any of this, Sarah?

23:36.850 --> 23:39.287
- No.
- Come on, Sarah.

23:39.330 --> 23:41.724
There's no way
we could've just gotten out.

23:41.768 --> 23:44.205
Somebody saved us,
and you know it.

23:44.248 --> 23:46.425
- Mija,

23:46.468 --> 23:47.687
what happened?

23:47.730 --> 23:49.384
- I'm sorry, but I have no idea

23:49.428 --> 23:50.559
what he's talking about.

23:50.603 --> 23:54.824
♪ ♪

23:54.868 --> 23:56.043
I don't, Dad.

23:58.001 --> 23:59.176
- You think you can, uh,

23:59.220 --> 24:02.615
describe this somebody for me?

24:02.658 --> 24:04.486
- Try not to let it bother you.

24:04.530 --> 24:05.879
This is what happens
with teenagers.

24:05.922 --> 24:07.010
They wanna be
with their friends

24:07.054 --> 24:08.185
more than their parents.

24:08.229 --> 24:09.360
- Yeah, but I loved hanging out

24:09.404 --> 24:10.971
with my mom
when I was their age.

24:11.014 --> 24:13.277
- [chuckles] It's one of the
many reasons I love you.

24:13.321 --> 24:15.279
- [scoffs]

24:15.323 --> 24:17.107
I know everybody says it
gets easier as they get older,

24:17.151 --> 24:20.023
but I guess the trade-off's
getting left behind.

24:20.067 --> 24:21.721
- I know, but our main job
as parents

24:21.764 --> 24:23.505
is to put ourselves
out of a job.

24:25.420 --> 24:27.509
♪ ♪

24:27.553 --> 24:29.859
You really think Peia's right
about Luthor?

24:29.903 --> 24:31.644
The world's better off
with him in prison

24:31.687 --> 24:33.907
even if he's innocent?

24:33.950 --> 24:35.691
- That's not for us to decide.

24:37.171 --> 24:38.346
All we can do
is tell the truth.

24:38.389 --> 24:39.739
You have to find out
what that is.

24:39.782 --> 24:42.176
- She's not gonna
tell me anything--

24:42.219 --> 24:44.091
at least not right now.

24:44.134 --> 24:46.833
- Then give her a reason to.

24:46.876 --> 24:48.748
Change her mind.
[door clicks open]

24:48.791 --> 24:50.750
- Matteo Mannheim just arrived.

24:50.793 --> 24:51.925
Okay if I send him in?

24:53.666 --> 24:55.537
- Give me a few more minutes
with her first.

24:55.581 --> 25:00.368
♪ ♪

25:00.411 --> 25:02.239
[door clicks shut]

25:02.283 --> 25:03.719
[high-pitched warbling]
- Dad, where are you?

25:03.763 --> 25:05.112
I need to talk to you.

25:05.155 --> 25:08.637
[whooshing]

25:08.681 --> 25:10.247
- Hey, is everything okay?

25:10.291 --> 25:11.945
- Dad, I really screwed up.
I think someone might've

25:11.988 --> 25:13.468
seen me out on Deacon's Road.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

25:13.512 --> 25:14.774
Slow down, slow down.
What happened?

25:14.817 --> 25:15.992
- So Sarah and George Junior,

25:16.036 --> 25:17.167
they were almost
in this car wreck,

25:17.211 --> 25:18.560
so I flew in
to try to save them,

25:18.604 --> 25:19.735
but I think George
might've seen me after.

25:19.779 --> 25:21.128
- Was anybody hurt?
- No, no.

25:21.171 --> 25:22.433
And I had my hood
and goggles on

25:22.477 --> 25:23.913
the whole time,
so I don't even think

25:23.957 --> 25:25.262
he saw my face.
- Okay, okay. Hey, hey.

25:25.306 --> 25:26.829
You did the right thing,
all right?

25:26.873 --> 25:28.178
Whatever Junior
thinks he saw,

25:28.222 --> 25:29.702
we can deal with later.

25:29.745 --> 25:31.094
- Okay.

25:33.053 --> 25:34.097
- Why do you smell like beer?

25:34.141 --> 25:37.318
♪ ♪

25:37.361 --> 25:38.841
- Okay.

25:38.885 --> 25:40.451
There was this party,

25:40.495 --> 25:42.976
and I had maybe
half a beer at most.

25:43.019 --> 25:44.934
- You were at a party?
- Yeah.

25:44.978 --> 25:47.067
Just sort of came up.

25:47.110 --> 25:49.156
- And was this before or after

25:49.199 --> 25:50.853
you and Jon canceled our plans?

25:50.897 --> 25:52.028
- I mean, does it matter?

25:52.072 --> 25:53.464
I just saved
two people's lives.

25:53.508 --> 25:55.554
- Yeah, and you also
lied to my face

25:55.597 --> 25:57.033
so you could go drink
at some party.

25:57.077 --> 25:58.600
- I--I told you it was nothing.

25:58.644 --> 26:00.123
- Oh, it's enough to get
you and Jon grounded.

26:00.167 --> 26:02.038
- You can't be serious
right now.

26:02.082 --> 26:03.300
- You keep giving me attitude,
you're gonna make it worse.

26:03.344 --> 26:05.085
- Yeah, whatever.
- Excuse me?

26:05.128 --> 26:06.782
- This isn't
about me having a beer.

26:06.826 --> 26:08.175
This is 'cause Jon and I
didn't wanna hang out with you.

26:08.218 --> 26:09.611
- Okay, Jordan,
get up to your room.

26:09.655 --> 26:10.830
- Yeah, I would rather
be there than watching

26:10.873 --> 26:11.874
some stupid
wrestling match anyway.

26:11.918 --> 26:13.354
- [sternly] Right now.

26:13.397 --> 26:15.095
[whooshing]

26:15.138 --> 26:20.535
♪ ♪

26:20.579 --> 26:22.189
- I can't believe
that Superman

26:22.232 --> 26:23.930
actually endorsed you.

26:23.973 --> 26:27.020
- I mean, worlds were merging.

26:27.063 --> 26:28.978
It wasn't a normal situation.

26:29.022 --> 26:31.459
- Best endorsement
I got my first term

26:31.502 --> 26:34.723
was from some big-shot rancher
out in Belleville,

26:34.767 --> 26:37.770
and it turns out, he was
selling psychedelic mushrooms

26:37.813 --> 26:40.076
to kids at K-State.
- You can't seriously

26:40.120 --> 26:42.818
be talking about
Diamond Dave Carlson.

26:42.862 --> 26:45.865
♪ ♪

26:45.908 --> 26:48.868
I mean, I did some
reporting on that story--

26:48.911 --> 26:50.783
crazy, crazy stuff.

26:52.001 --> 26:54.047
[door clicks open,
bells jingle]

26:55.918 --> 26:57.354
[door clicks shut,
bells jingle]

26:57.398 --> 26:59.313
♪ ♪

26:59.356 --> 27:00.706
Um, it's for you.

27:02.708 --> 27:04.840
- Uh, if you'll excuse me.

27:06.755 --> 27:08.061
- Who is that anyway?

27:08.104 --> 27:10.106
- It's just her ex-husband.

27:10.150 --> 27:11.934
- Why did you
get up first, then?

27:11.978 --> 27:15.242
♪ ♪

27:15.285 --> 27:17.940
- Uh, I'm sorry to pull you
away from all this,

27:17.984 --> 27:19.768
but, um,

27:19.812 --> 27:22.466
first off, Sarah is okay.

27:22.510 --> 27:24.904
Nobody was hurt.
- What happened?

27:24.947 --> 27:26.383
- She was drinking.

27:26.427 --> 27:27.471
- [sighs]
- Totaled her car.

27:27.515 --> 27:29.517
- Oh, my God.
- Yeah.

27:29.560 --> 27:32.041
Uh, Deputy Johnson

27:32.085 --> 27:34.565
is charging her with a DUI,

27:34.609 --> 27:35.958
but she's agreed to release her

27:36.002 --> 27:37.699
into our custody,
and I thought

27:37.743 --> 27:39.135
that it'd be best
if we handled this

27:39.179 --> 27:41.181
on a unified front.

27:41.224 --> 27:43.226
- Yeah, okay, all right.

27:43.270 --> 27:47.491
Just--I need a moment.

27:47.535 --> 27:49.537
- Is that
Mayor Lang's daughter?

27:49.580 --> 27:50.973
- I'm not really sure.

27:51.017 --> 27:52.366
Is it?

27:52.409 --> 27:56.152
♪ ♪

27:56.196 --> 27:59.112
- [sighs]

27:59.155 --> 28:02.158
♪ ♪

28:02.202 --> 28:04.465
Governor Wexler,
I am so sorry.

28:04.508 --> 28:05.596
- Is everything okay?

28:05.640 --> 28:07.250
- Yeah, just a small matter

28:07.294 --> 28:09.426
that needs my attention.

28:11.428 --> 28:14.170
- Uh, looks like
you've got your hands full,

28:14.214 --> 28:16.999
Mayor Lang, so, um, good luck.

28:17.043 --> 28:23.005
♪ ♪

28:23.049 --> 28:24.528
- Why don't you call the car?

28:24.572 --> 28:27.401
- She really is
a fantastic mayor.

28:27.444 --> 28:30.709
[door clicks shut,
bells jingle]

28:30.752 --> 28:34.016
- [whispering indistinctly]

28:34.060 --> 28:36.236
- What is wrong with you?

28:36.279 --> 28:38.978
I thought if anyone
could understand, you would.

28:39.021 --> 28:41.371
Can't you just
let me die in peace?

28:41.415 --> 28:43.199
- You need to let me help you.

28:43.243 --> 28:45.158
- [scoffs]
By setting Luthor free?

28:45.201 --> 28:46.376
Not happening.

28:46.420 --> 28:48.117
- This isn't about him.

28:48.161 --> 28:50.119
This is about what kind
of example you're setting

28:50.163 --> 28:51.686
for Matteo.

28:51.730 --> 28:54.689
- Do not use my son
as leverage.

28:54.733 --> 28:56.299
- You've lied to him
his whole life.

28:56.343 --> 28:58.693
- I am a good mom.

28:58.737 --> 29:01.174
- But is that
what he's gonna remember,

29:01.217 --> 29:02.828
or will it be all the things

29:02.871 --> 29:04.830
he's gonna read about you,

29:04.873 --> 29:07.267
all the people
that you've hurt?

29:07.310 --> 29:08.877
- Matteo knows my heart.

29:08.921 --> 29:11.445
- But you have hidden
so much from him.

29:11.488 --> 29:13.403
He must have
so many questions.

29:13.447 --> 29:16.885
♪ ♪

29:16.929 --> 29:19.496
- I never wanted him involved

29:19.540 --> 29:22.195
in any of this.

29:22.238 --> 29:23.892
My life,

29:23.936 --> 29:25.807
the mistakes I've made,

29:25.851 --> 29:28.375
it was all so that he
wouldn't have to make

29:28.418 --> 29:30.986
those kind of choices.

29:31.030 --> 29:33.293
- Matteo deserves
the truth, Peia.

29:35.164 --> 29:37.384
Show your son
you have regrets.

29:37.427 --> 29:38.994
Be the example he needs.

29:39.038 --> 29:40.735
Let that be a part
of your legacy.

29:42.693 --> 29:43.782
- I can't.

29:43.825 --> 29:44.870
- Yes, you can.

29:46.872 --> 29:48.961
- [sighs] No.

29:50.440 --> 29:52.007
Not without seeing him.

29:52.051 --> 29:54.618
It's just--it's important

29:54.662 --> 29:56.229
he hears it from me first.

29:58.840 --> 30:01.712
- Then you'll
tell me everything,

30:01.756 --> 30:02.975
even about Luthor?

30:03.018 --> 30:09.024
♪ ♪

30:10.460 --> 30:11.897
Send him in.

30:11.940 --> 30:13.333
- Wait.

30:13.376 --> 30:15.117
He's here?

30:15.161 --> 30:16.858
- Make this right
with your son.

30:19.034 --> 30:21.384
We can talk after.

30:21.428 --> 30:23.299
- Can you take these off

30:23.343 --> 30:25.432
so I can at least hug my son?

30:25.475 --> 30:32.526
♪ ♪

30:33.919 --> 30:35.311
[sighs]

30:35.355 --> 30:36.312
Sweetheart.

30:36.356 --> 30:39.098
♪ ♪

30:39.141 --> 30:40.142
- Hey, Mom.

30:44.494 --> 30:45.931
- I'm so sorry.

30:45.974 --> 30:47.715
I wasn't planning on driving.

30:47.758 --> 30:48.890
It's--

30:48.934 --> 30:50.065
the sheriff came,
and everything

30:50.109 --> 30:51.588
happened so fast, and I just--

30:51.632 --> 30:53.590
- Drove drunk?
- I wasn't drunk.

30:53.634 --> 30:56.376
- We are not gonna debate
how drunk you were, Sarah.

30:56.419 --> 30:58.204
You had alcohol
in your system,

30:58.247 --> 30:59.292
and you got
behind the wheel.

30:59.335 --> 31:00.728
That is never okay.

31:00.771 --> 31:02.251
- I know.
I know I messed up.

31:02.295 --> 31:03.905
- Yeah, you're damn rightyou did.

31:03.949 --> 31:06.125
- I am so disappointed
in you right now.

31:06.168 --> 31:07.735
- What if something would've
happened to you, Sarah,

31:07.778 --> 31:11.173
or--or Junior, huh?

31:11.217 --> 31:12.958
The two of you should be dead.

31:13.001 --> 31:14.524
- Dad.
- And you still haven't

31:14.568 --> 31:15.612
been straight with me
about what really

31:15.656 --> 31:17.745
happened out there either.

31:17.788 --> 31:19.225
- What do you mean?

31:19.268 --> 31:21.357
- Dad thinks
that some superhero

31:21.401 --> 31:23.490
rescued us from the crash.

31:24.926 --> 31:26.841
- Who, Superman?
- No.

31:26.885 --> 31:29.148
Uh, someone else.

31:31.237 --> 31:33.326
- Junior said he saw somebody.

31:33.369 --> 31:34.893
- [scoffs] Kyle.

31:34.936 --> 31:36.372
- Lana, if you'd seen
the accident,

31:36.416 --> 31:37.417
you'd know that
that's the only thing

31:37.460 --> 31:38.679
that makes any damn sense.

31:38.722 --> 31:40.420
- Why would Sarah be lying?

31:40.463 --> 31:42.161
- Why would Junior?

31:42.204 --> 31:43.902
Look, something happened
out there, okay?

31:43.945 --> 31:44.903
I know it did.

31:44.946 --> 31:48.036
[dramatic music]

31:48.080 --> 31:49.995
- [scoffs]

31:50.038 --> 31:53.085
I--I don't know what
you want me to say, Kyle.

31:53.128 --> 31:56.523
♪ ♪

31:56.566 --> 31:58.917
- Okay, Lana, you know what?
You handle this, all right?

31:58.960 --> 32:01.354
'Cause I don't really wanna
be around either one of y'all

32:01.397 --> 32:02.485
right now.

32:02.529 --> 32:06.272
♪ ♪

32:06.315 --> 32:07.316
[door clicks open]

32:09.101 --> 32:10.537
[door clicks shut]

32:10.580 --> 32:13.801
- Look at you.

32:13.844 --> 32:15.759
You even figured out
how to tie it.

32:15.803 --> 32:18.110
- [chuckles]Yeah.

32:18.153 --> 32:19.938
Wasn't easy without you.

32:22.244 --> 32:23.376
None of it is.

32:23.419 --> 32:25.465
♪ ♪

32:25.508 --> 32:27.597
- I'm just glad you're here.

32:28.729 --> 32:30.905
- Me too.

32:30.949 --> 32:32.211
- [sniffles]

32:32.254 --> 32:34.300
[sighs]

32:34.343 --> 32:36.432
About that night

32:36.476 --> 32:37.477
at Little Ace's--

32:37.520 --> 32:39.653
- No, no, Mom, Mom.

32:39.696 --> 32:41.829
You don't have to do this.

32:41.872 --> 32:43.918
- No, it's important.

32:43.962 --> 32:45.659
I need you to know the truth.

32:47.356 --> 32:48.792
- I talked to Dad.

32:50.620 --> 32:53.145
He told me everything.

32:53.188 --> 32:56.583
- What do you mean--
what do you mean everything?

32:56.626 --> 32:58.846
- I know what he's
been working on.

32:58.889 --> 33:02.197
♪ ♪

33:02.241 --> 33:03.285
The cure.

33:03.329 --> 33:05.722
- Oh, Matteo.

33:05.766 --> 33:06.941
I love your father,

33:06.985 --> 33:09.378
but--but he's desperate, and--

33:09.422 --> 33:10.814
- No, no, Mom, Mom.

33:10.858 --> 33:12.555
It works.

33:14.340 --> 33:16.298
It works.
That's--

33:16.342 --> 33:19.171
that's why I'm here.

33:19.214 --> 33:22.739
♪ ♪

33:22.783 --> 33:24.089
Now, Dad said
it wouldn't take long

33:24.132 --> 33:25.351
for it to kick in,

33:25.394 --> 33:27.614
and then after,

33:27.657 --> 33:30.704
you come find us at the place
where it all started.

33:30.747 --> 33:32.140
- Oh.

33:32.184 --> 33:37.319
♪ ♪

33:37.363 --> 33:39.365
- A month is a little extreme,Clark.

33:39.408 --> 33:40.931
- Lois, he lied,
and he was drinking.

33:40.975 --> 33:42.194
I mean, fine.

33:42.237 --> 33:43.195
He's grounded for two weeks--

33:43.238 --> 33:44.587
no powers, no fortress.

33:44.631 --> 33:45.806
- We'll talk about it
when I get home.

33:45.849 --> 33:47.199
What did Jonathan have to say?

33:47.242 --> 33:49.375
- He's not back yet.
- Is he driving?

33:49.418 --> 33:51.159
Do you know if he was drinking?
- I don't know. I don't know.

33:51.203 --> 33:52.291
He's probably
with Candice somewhere.

33:52.334 --> 33:54.249
- Everything okay?

33:54.293 --> 33:55.511
- You need to find him, Clark.

33:55.555 --> 33:57.339
- Okay, okay, just hold on.

33:57.383 --> 33:59.080
[high-pitched warbling]
Wait.

33:59.124 --> 34:01.213
[engine rumbling]

34:01.256 --> 34:03.432
He just pulled up.
[engine shuts off]

34:03.476 --> 34:04.781
I'll call you back.

34:07.088 --> 34:08.610
Jonathan!
- What the hell, Dad?

34:08.655 --> 34:09.656
- If you were
drinking and driving,

34:09.699 --> 34:10.612
we are selling this truck!

34:10.657 --> 34:11.745
- I wasn't drinking.

34:11.788 --> 34:12.746
- But you were at a party!

34:12.789 --> 34:14.226
- Where I drank water.

34:14.268 --> 34:15.792
Look, if--if I was drinking,

34:15.835 --> 34:17.228
you'd be able to,
like, super-smell it

34:17.272 --> 34:19.666
or something.

34:19.708 --> 34:21.188
- Okay, well,
your brother was drinking.

34:21.233 --> 34:22.625
- Okay.

34:22.668 --> 34:26.063
So do you want me
to apologize for him now?

34:26.107 --> 34:28.109
Look, after everything
that happened last year,

34:28.152 --> 34:30.068
there's no way I would be
drinking and driving.

34:30.110 --> 34:31.460
You don't have
to worry about that.

34:31.504 --> 34:32.547
- Okay, okay, I believe you.

34:32.592 --> 34:34.159
Just--

34:34.202 --> 34:35.856
but you lied to me
about the party.

34:35.899 --> 34:37.379
- Okay, sure.

34:37.422 --> 34:39.338
Maybe we should've
told you about that,

34:39.380 --> 34:42.384
but we were just trying
not to hurt your feelings.

34:42.428 --> 34:44.864
- [chuckles]
[stammers]

34:44.908 --> 34:46.780
I just think it's important
we spend time together.

34:46.822 --> 34:48.260
You guys are
growing up so fast.

34:48.303 --> 34:51.524
- Okay, well, you're the one
who's always busy.

34:51.567 --> 34:53.047
Like, we can't just sit around

34:53.091 --> 34:55.136
and wait for you
to have free time,

34:55.179 --> 34:56.746
especially since
I haven't seen Candice

34:56.790 --> 34:58.748
in, like, a month.

34:58.792 --> 35:00.402
That's not how it works.

35:00.446 --> 35:04.754
♪ ♪

35:04.798 --> 35:06.495
Can I have my keys back now?

35:06.539 --> 35:09.063
♪ ♪

35:09.107 --> 35:10.934
Thank you.

35:10.978 --> 35:17.898
♪ ♪

35:17.941 --> 35:19.726
[lock beeps]

35:19.769 --> 35:21.206
- Now that the kid
finally left,

35:21.249 --> 35:23.121
you need to get
that confession.

35:23.164 --> 35:25.645
Probably gonna be
your last shot.

35:25.688 --> 35:27.342
Sure you don't want me
to come with?

35:27.386 --> 35:29.823
- Yeah, it's best
if I finish this.

35:29.866 --> 35:35.089
♪ ♪

35:35.133 --> 35:38.832
[power dampener thrumming]

35:38.875 --> 35:40.660
I'm glad you got
to see Matteo.

35:42.531 --> 35:44.229
I know this isn't easy,

35:44.272 --> 35:47.623
but you promised you would
be honest about Luthor.

35:47.667 --> 35:49.843
- That was before.

35:49.886 --> 35:51.149
- Before what?

35:52.802 --> 35:54.500
- Before I got better.

35:54.543 --> 35:57.764
[suspenseful music]

35:57.807 --> 36:00.158
♪ ♪

36:00.201 --> 36:02.334
You're gonna help me
get out of here, Lois.

36:02.377 --> 36:05.380
[intense humming]

36:08.818 --> 36:11.778
- Take me out of here.

36:11.821 --> 36:13.649
[static crackling]

36:13.693 --> 36:16.348
[suspenseful music]

36:16.391 --> 36:20.047
♪ ♪

36:20.090 --> 36:22.919
- Get me out of here--now,

36:22.963 --> 36:24.530
or I'll bring
this whole building down.

36:24.573 --> 36:27.185
♪ ♪

36:27.228 --> 36:29.187
- You've reached
the voice mail of Lois Lane.

36:29.230 --> 36:31.841
Leave a message, and I'll call
you back as soon as I can.

36:34.322 --> 36:35.367
- Kyle?

36:35.410 --> 36:38.370
[dramatic music]

36:38.413 --> 36:41.982
♪ ♪

36:42.025 --> 36:44.158
Hey, Kyle.
What's going on?

36:45.159 --> 36:46.508
- Is Jon here?

36:46.552 --> 36:47.596
- Uh, yeah, he's upstairs.

36:47.640 --> 36:49.424
- I need to talk to him.

36:49.468 --> 36:50.556
It's about Sarah.

36:50.599 --> 36:51.861
- Everything okay?

36:51.905 --> 36:54.081
- Luckily, yeah--

36:54.124 --> 36:56.562
'cause of him.

36:56.605 --> 36:58.128
- I'm--
[chuckles]

36:58.172 --> 37:00.218
I'm sorry, I don't understand.

37:00.261 --> 37:01.828
- I'm pretty sure you do.

37:01.871 --> 37:04.396
♪ ♪

37:04.439 --> 37:06.441
- What's Mr. Cushing saying?

37:06.485 --> 37:08.487
- He thinks
you have superpowers.

37:08.530 --> 37:11.141
- Me?

37:11.185 --> 37:14.057
[electricity zapping]

37:14.101 --> 37:15.842
- You realize you've made
your son an accomplice?

37:15.885 --> 37:17.322
He's a part of this now.

37:17.365 --> 37:19.106
- It doesn't matter.
We'll protect him.

37:19.149 --> 37:21.021
[electricity zapping]

37:21.064 --> 37:22.675
Unlock it.
- I can't.

37:22.718 --> 37:25.373
- Unlock it.
- I don't have access.

37:25.417 --> 37:26.679
- What's on the other side?

37:26.722 --> 37:28.550
- The control room
that leads outside.

37:28.594 --> 37:30.987
- How many people are in there?
- You blow these doors,

37:31.031 --> 37:32.250
every alarm in the building
will go off

37:32.293 --> 37:34.295
and Superman
will be here in seconds.

37:34.339 --> 37:35.862
Don't do this.

37:35.905 --> 37:39.605
[suspenseful music]

37:39.648 --> 37:42.999
- I really do wish
things had been different.

37:43.043 --> 37:45.654
In another life,
we would've been great friends.

37:45.698 --> 37:48.222
- Peia, please.
- Sorry, Lois.

37:48.266 --> 37:50.964
[intense humming]

37:51.007 --> 37:53.053
- What's going on?
[indistinct yelling]

37:53.096 --> 37:54.968
Lock it down!

37:59.146 --> 38:02.584
[indistinct yelling]

38:02.628 --> 38:04.412
Lock it down!

38:04.456 --> 38:07.241
- [screams]

38:10.766 --> 38:15.118
♪ ♪

38:15.162 --> 38:17.120
[sirens wailing]

38:17.164 --> 38:18.470
- He was at the party.

38:18.513 --> 38:19.906
- Oh, but so were
lots of kids.

38:19.949 --> 38:21.211
- And--and--and he was there

38:21.255 --> 38:22.691
the night
when the fire at Fowe's

38:22.735 --> 38:24.563
turned into a damn snow globe.

38:24.606 --> 38:26.086
I mean, come on, Kent.

38:26.129 --> 38:27.566
I know he's got powers.

38:27.609 --> 38:28.784
- Kyle, you're wrong.

38:28.828 --> 38:30.351
[dramatic music]

38:30.395 --> 38:32.919
- Everything started
when your family moved here,

38:32.962 --> 38:35.487
and Jon has been at the center
of all of this.

38:35.530 --> 38:37.967
[high-pitched warbling]

38:38.011 --> 38:40.013
[people screaming]

38:40.056 --> 38:41.406
- Kyle, you--you need to leave.

38:41.449 --> 38:43.321
- No, I will leave
when I get some answers.

38:43.364 --> 38:45.410
[explosions booming]
- We'll talk about this later.

38:45.453 --> 38:47.716
- We can talk about this now.

38:47.760 --> 38:50.023
- I have to go!
- Just--

38:50.066 --> 38:52.895
please tell me the truth.

38:52.939 --> 38:55.245
♪ ♪

38:55.289 --> 38:56.682
I know it was him.

38:56.725 --> 38:58.466
- No, it wasn't!

38:58.510 --> 39:05.517
♪ ♪

39:06.561 --> 39:08.084
Go home, Kyle.

39:09.782 --> 39:11.174
I'll explain it all
to you tomorrow.

39:12.698 --> 39:15.527
[whooshing]

39:15.570 --> 39:18.573
- [panting]

39:20.445 --> 39:23.448
[people screaming]

39:25.885 --> 39:28.278
[people screaming]

39:30.324 --> 39:34.067
[sirens wailing, gunfire]

39:34.110 --> 39:35.808
- Peia.

39:35.851 --> 39:41.030
♪ ♪

39:41.074 --> 39:43.381
[alarm blaring]

39:43.424 --> 39:45.426
- Full lockdown
is now in effect.

39:45.470 --> 39:48.821
All medical staff report
to the infirmary at once.

39:48.864 --> 39:51.998
Repeat, full lockdown
is now in effect.

39:52.041 --> 39:55.088
All medical staff report
to the infirmary at once.

39:55.131 --> 39:56.916
♪ ♪

39:56.959 --> 39:58.874
- Superman.

39:58.918 --> 39:59.962
- Peia?

40:00.006 --> 40:01.268
- She's gone.

40:01.311 --> 40:08.362
♪ ♪

40:12.410 --> 40:15.413
[footsteps tapping]

40:20.505 --> 40:21.767
- [sighs]

40:21.810 --> 40:23.899
♪ ♪

40:23.943 --> 40:24.944
- Mom?

40:24.987 --> 40:26.772
♪ ♪

40:26.815 --> 40:28.469
Mom.

40:28.513 --> 40:30.210
Mom.

40:30.253 --> 40:37.304
♪ ♪

40:43.963 --> 40:46.313
- You did it.

40:46.356 --> 40:47.619
- We did it.

40:47.662 --> 40:51.449
♪ ♪

40:51.492 --> 40:53.712
- [chuckles]

40:53.755 --> 41:00.762
♪ ♪

41:25.918 --> 41:28.921
- Greg, move your head.
